An early, hard to find book from one of my favorite creators. Very much to my complete amazement, somebody has one graded 9.6 on ebay right now with a $129 buy it now price. lol Comic collecting is a funny thing.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

'Floyd Farland, Man of the Future'

Eclipse Books, 1987, 51 pages

Written and Illustrated by Chris Ware

Visually, this books is NOTHING like any of Ware's later work. Done in a large blocky black style, none of the intricacies and detail of his later books is apparent here. It's well-written, though, and funny, even if his apparent belief that most everything kind of sucks and none of us are achieving our full potential is already clear. Oh... and he's already saying, 'god...', which made me laugh.

